  "body": "HTML doesn't have a concept of **scope**, but it do use concept like **variable** at many where(like `<input id=\"abc\"/><label for=\"abc\">abc</label>`). We should add **scope** to html.\r\n\r\nMaybe you say \"for label, we can wrap input in label\", but it changes the html structure, and there are many other scene using html variable like [spectre](https://picturepan2.github.io/spectre/experimentals.html#filters).\r\n\r\nSo why not add an api `this.instance_id` or `this.generate_id(abc: string) => this.instance_id + '/' + abc` or whatever others can make html scope.",
